chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA if you have fits.
chunks.plain_content:
Fits and driving
You must tell DVLA if you have fits.

chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you do not tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. If you’re involved in an accident, you may be prosecuted.
chunks.plain_content:
Fits and driving
You can be fined up to £1,000 if you do not tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. If you’re involved in an accident, you may be prosecuted.

chunks.html_content:
You must tell DVLA.

Fill in the form FEP1 and send it to DVLA. The address is on the form.
